If there are no duplicates, return None.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef find_duplicate(lst: list[int]) -> int | None:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `lst` (list[int]): A list of unique integers.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- The first duplicate integer in the input list. If there are no duplicates, return `None`.\", \"code\": \"def find_duplicate(lst: list[int]) -> int | None:\\n    seen = set()\\n    for num in lst:\\n        if num in seen:\\n            return num\\n        seen.add(num)\\n    return None\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert find_duplicate([1, 2, 3, 4, 5]) == None\", \"assert find_duplicate([1, 2, 3, 4, 3]) == 3\", \"assert find_duplicate([-1, -2, -3, -4, -5]) == None\", \"assert find_duplicate([1, 2, 3, 4, 4]) == 4\"] }"
